If you are C programmer you might have noticed the existence of the bit fields in structs:
typedef struct {
int Some : 1;
int Bit : 2;
int Fields : 5;
} MyStruct;
Marshaling that code could be a pain in the ass. Before all, read Jonathan's doc, then forget about the C's sizeof, sum all the bit fields and get the value, in our sample struct we need to get that as 1 byte (1 + 2 + 5 = 8 bits = 1 byte) and then use the System.

